Juicy, smoky, and bursting with coastal spices — this Kerala-style grilled chicken is marinated in a bold blend of pepper, garlic, and curry leaves, then grilled to perfection. Each bite brings the heat and heart of Kerala to your plate! 🔥🌴🍗

Peri Peri Cheesy balls 🥔 

Rainy days + cheesy potato balls = comfort in every bite ☔🧀🥔

Golden on the outside, gooey on the inside, they’re the kind of snack that makes you want to cozy up by the window with a hot cup of chai and just be. 😍🤌🏼

Simple, nostalgic, and oh-so-satisfying!

Paneer Ghotala 🫶🏼

It’s spicy, it’s street style but it’s high protein exclamation ‼️ 

One of my favourite ways to make a paneer Sabzi at home. Comes together in no time and it’s super tasty.

Burnt Garlic Noodles 🌶️☔ — because no monsoon is complete without a plate of spicy desi Chinese!
That bold garlic kick, smoky wok-tossed noodles, and the perfect chilli heat—it’s comfort, nostalgia, and a little chaos, just like the rains.
Slurp it hot while thunder rumbles outside. Who’s with me? 💥🍜

Honey Chilli Garlic Prawns + Rainy Weekend = Pure Bliss 🍤🌧️
There’s something magical about the sound of rain, the sizzle of prawns in a pan, and that perfect sweet-spicy kick to go with your favourite drink.
Curl up, unwind, and let this be your cozy weekend indulgence. ✨🍷🌶️

Bringing the streets of Amritsar to your screens with my Punjabi partner-in-crime @kriti_kaur_dhiman ✨ We teamed up to make the ultimate street-style Nutri Kulcha – spicy soya masala, buttery kulchas, and all the desi vibes 🌶🫓 This one’s straight from the heart… and Punjab 💛

3 Chicken Marinades, 1 @embercookware pan, endless flavor 🍗✨
From smoky Chicken Tikka, to zesty Pudhina Chutney Chicken, to herby Italian-style Chicken — these marinades are perfect to have an as appetiser, a whole meal with salad and carbs or meal prepping for the week.

I’m using my go-to Ember cookware for that perfect sear and even cook every single time. Trust me — once you try these, boring chicken is officially cancelled.

🔥 Which one are you trying first — Indian, herby, or minty fresh?

Recipes :

Classic Tandoori Marination: 🍗🌶
- 1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste
- 1 tbsp red chili powder
- 1 tsp cumin powder
- 1.5 tbsp coriander powder
- 2 tsp garam masala
- Pinch of turmeric powder
- Half cup yogurt

Pudina Chutney Marinade: 🍗🌿
- 1 tbsp coriander powder
- 1 tsp cumin powder
- 1 tsp garam masala
- ½ tsp turmeric powder
- 2 tbsp yogurt
- Mint chutney (made with ½ cup mint leaves, ⅓ cup coriander leaves, 2 green chilies, ½ inch ginger, 3 garlic cloves, 1 tsp cumin powder, salt to taste)

Italian Herb Chicken Marination:🍗🧄🍋‍🟩
- 1 tbsp lemon juice
- 2 tbsp garlic, chopped
- 1 tbsp chili flakes
- 1 tsp black pepper powder
- Coriander leaves
- Olive oil
